§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We generalize the notion of angles in the plane to angles
    in space. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬angle❭ (❬unsigned angle❭) between $x ∈ 𝗥^3$ and $y ∈
    𝗥^3$ is the real number
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ θ = ∠(x, y) = \cos^{-1}\frac{x^⊤ y}{\norm{x}\norm{y}} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

